Excuse me. Is there a room available?
I'd like to rent a room for a while.\n< Serena>

Ah, we do have rooms available... How
long do you plan to stay?\n< Innkeeper>

It's undecided. For now, I'd like to pay
with this.\n< Serena>
CommonPopupManager.showInfo({},'100Ｇ Paid.',null)
Oh?! ...My, my.\n< Innkeeper>

I'd also like meals and a bed prepared.
If there's anything lacking, I'll pay
more later.\n< Serena>

Lacking? ...This amount is more than
enough for a 100-day stay.\n< Innkeeper>
Is that so.\n< Serena>

By the way, I'd like to take a bath.
Does this inn have a bath available?\n< Serena>

In this town, we have hot springs, and
for bathing, we guide our guests there.\n< Innkeeper>
Hot springs? There's such a thing here?\n< Serena>

\n< Innkeeper>The hot springs are located in the
building to the southwest of the town.
If you leave the inn and follow the
road, you'll get there in no time.

\n< Innkeeper>We will have your room ready by the time
you return.

\n< Serena>Hmm, then I shall go check it out. I'm
counting on you for the room.

\n< Innkeeper>Your room isn't ready yet, so please
enjoy the hot springs in the meantime.

\n< Innkeeper>Good morning. Did you sleep well last
night?

plans for today?

To the tool shop. I need to stop by
there.\n< Serena>

side of town.

If you leave the inn and walk straight
ahead, you'll get there shortly.\n< Innkeeper>
\n< Serena>I see, thank you. Then I'll be off.
\n< Innkeeper>Take care.

\n< Serena>It looks delicious, but I'm not hungry
right now.

\n< Serena>This must be the private room of the
shopkeeper- sama. Let's not enter...
It's a box.\n< Serena>

Hmm... Why am I examining something like
this?\n< Serena>
It's a box.\n< Serena>

There doesn't seem to be anything of
use.\n< Serena>
It's a barrel.\n< Serena>

It seems to contain drinking water.
Let's not touch it.\n< Serena>
It's a fireplace.\n< Serena>

I glanced at the guest book earlier, and
it seems there are people who stay in
the space in front of this fireplace.\n< Serena>

It's surprising that such a place is
rented out, but even more surprising are
those who stay there. How do they manage
to sleep...\n< Serena>
The menu and such are written here.\n< Serena>
There's no brioche...\n< Serena>

Should I invest to expand the lineup to
include it? I'm seriously considering
it.\n< Serena>
Please knock before you use it.\n< Serena>
...\n< Serena>

Ah, I see. It's to check if someone's
already inside.\n< Serena>
It's flour or something.\n< Serena>

It's well-milled. It'll probably make
delicious bread.\n< Serena>
It's an apple. It's still green.\n< Serena>
W-Wonder if it'll turn into a key...\n< Serena>
It's a stove.\n< Serena>

Cooking, huh? Mother might not approve,
but I'm a bit interested.\n< Serena>
Garlic and onions are hanging.\n< Serena>

These guys are bad news. They must be
receiving a public punishment as an
example.\n< Serena>

I hope this experience makes them a bit
sweeter.\n< Serena>
There's alcohol placed over there.\n< Serena>

I'm not particularly interested, but
it's a bit irritating how it's
ostentatiously placed just out of reach.\n< Serena>
It's a bag of flour.\n< Serena>
It looks too heavy for me to lift.\n< Serena>
